country.name: New Zealand
country.overview: New Zealand is a country in the southwestern Pacific Ocean consisting of 2 main islands, both marked by volcanoes and glaciation. Capital Wellington, on the North Island, is home to Te Papa Tongarewa, the expansive national museum. Wellington’s dramatic Mt. Victoria, along with the South Island’s Fiordland and Southern Lakes, stood in for mythical Middle Earth in Peter Jackson’s \"Lord of the Rings\" films.

geography.location_description: Oceania, islands in the South Pacific Ocean, southeast of Australia
geography.area_note: almost twice the size of North Carolina; about the size of Colorado
geography.terrain: predominately mountainous with large coastal plains
geography.hazards: earthquakes are common, though usually not severe; volcanic activity
geography.notes: almost 90% of the population lives in cities; Wellington is the southernmost national capital in the world
